==English==

===Etymology===
Abbreviation of '''M'''other '''I''''d '''L'''ike to '''F'''uck. Popularized by the film ''[[w:American Pie_(movie)|American Pie]]'' (1999), though its usage predates the movie.

===Pronunciation===
*[[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|IPA]]: /<tt>mɪɫf</tt>/
*[[Wiktionary:Pronunciation_key|SAMPA]]: /<tt>mI5f</tt>/

==={{acronym}}===
'''MILF'''  (''plural:'' '''[[MILFs]]''') 
# {{vulgar}}: A [[mother]] found sexually attractive.  ''(Functions as a noun.)''
#:''Tom's mother is hot &mdash; she's a real '''MILF'''.''
# {{vulgar}} A woman of seeming motherly age or appearance found sexually attractive, regardless of actual motherhood status
# ''(less popular, [[bowdlerize]]d):'' "Mama Is Looking Fine."

==={{initialism}}===
# '''M'''oro '''I'''slamic '''L'''iberation '''F'''ront, an organization in the Philippines seeking to establish an Islamic state on the island of Mindanao.  Distinctly different from the [[MNLF]] or Moro National Liberation Front which, though has a similar goal, is composed of different leaders.

===Usage note===
''MILF'' has quickly become a much used descriptor on the internet for pornography sites featuring women mostly between the ages of 35 and 50.